mlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mover> <mi>X</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">¯</mo> </mover> </mrow> <mo>∼</mo> <mrow> <mtext>N</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mi>μ</mi> <mrow> <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext> </mrow> <mfrac> <mn>4</mn> <mrow> <mn>100</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\" \\Rightarrow {\\text{P}}\\left( {\\frac{{\\bar X - \\mu }}{{\\frac{2}{{10}}}} < \\frac{{60.33 - \\mu }}{{\\frac{2}{{10}}}}} \\right) = 0.25\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo> <mrow> <mtext>P</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <mover> <mi>X</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">¯</mo> </mover> </mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mi>μ</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mfrac> <mn>2</mn> <mrow> <mn>10</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>&lt;</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>60.33</mn> <mo>−</mo> <mi>μ</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mfrac> <mn>2</mn> <mrow> <mn>10</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0.25</mn> </math></span><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\" \\Rightarrow {\\text{P}}\\left( {Z < \\frac{{60.33 - \\mu }}{{\\frac{2}{{10}}}}} \\right) = 0.25\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo> <mrow> <mtext>P</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mi>Z</mi> <mo>&lt;</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>60.33</mn> <mo>−</mo> <mi>μ</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mfrac> <mn>2</mn> <mrow> <mn>10</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0.25</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; where&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"Z \\sim {\\text{N}}\\left( {0{\\text{, }}{1^2}} \\right)\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>Z</mi> <mo>∼</mo> <mrow> <mtext>N</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mn>0</mn> <mrow> <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{60.33 - \\mu }}{{\\frac{2}{{10}}}} =&nbsp; - 0.6744 \\ldots \" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>60.33</mn> <mo>−</mo> <mi>μ</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mfrac> <mn>2</mn> <mrow> <mn>10</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mn>0.6744</mn> <mo>…</mo> </math></span><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\mu&nbsp; = 60.33 + \\frac{2}{{10}} \\times 0.6744 \\ldots \" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>μ</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>60.33</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mfrac> <mn>2</mn> <mrow> <mn>10</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>×</mo> <mn>0.6744</mn> <mo>…</mo> </math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\mu&nbsp; = 60.5\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>μ</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>60.5</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17422","referenceCode":"19N.3.AHL.TZ0.Hsp_3c.iii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Given that the probability that Josie makes a Type II error is 0.25, find the value of μ , giving your answer correct to three significant figures.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"c.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.18—T and Z test, type I and II errors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}